analysis: The documents primarily concern the transfer, modification, or reservation of land, often involving military reservations and other government entities like the Coast Guard or Lighthouse Service. A recurring theme is the adjustment of land boundaries and usage rights in Hawaii, with references to specific locations, coordinates, and legal statutes. Some documents also involve the establishment or revocation of reservations for military or naval purposes in other locations like the Canal Zone and California.
title: Land Management and Military Use Adjustments
